    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>On the Grand Day for Bush, American Voices</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard Toh letter on Maureen Dowd's Aug 2 column says former Pres Bush has been conducting himself more honorably during presidential campaign than Pres Clinton has</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Maureen Dowd writes (column, Aug. 2) that ''the race turns out to be what we thought it was all along: President Bush vs. President Clinton.'' Indeed, President Clinton has been behaving less than presidential by taking every opportunity to take a cheap shot at George W. Bush.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Maureen Dowd writes (column, Aug. 2) that ''the race turns out to be what we thought it was all along: President Bush vs. President Clinton.'' Indeed, President Clinton has been behaving less than presidential by taking every opportunity to take a cheap shot at George W. Bush.</p>
        <p>This election is best left to  the candidates, and the better candidate will emerge as the winner. Former President Bush has been honorable. His reactions were reasonable in light of the attacks made on his family.</p>
        <p>RICHARD TOH  Bensalem, Pa., Aug. 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
